Sentencas: The high-pressure performance of lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM), LSM-zirconia, and LSM/ceria composite electrodes was studied by impedance spectroscopy and dc methods.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: Electrode resistances decreased in proportion to P(O-2)(1/2) for the LSM electrode in both cathodic and anodic directions to at least 10MPa (similar to 100 atm), a decrease that was attributed to dissociative oxygen adsorption and related phenomena.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: For the LSM-20/zirconia composite electrode, resistances decreased in proportion to P(O-2)(1/4) across the entire pressure range considered.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: Two principal features appeared in the impedance spectra, one that showed a P(O-2)(1/4) dependence attributed to charge transfer reactions, and a smaller feature that was nearly pressure-independent possibly due to transport in the zirconia portion of the composite.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: For the LSM-20/ceria composite electrode, resistances decreased as P(O-2)(0,3 0,4) at high pressure, depending on temperature.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: Two features appeared in the impedance spectra: one at low to intermediate frequency having a similar to P(O-2)(1/2) dependence and a second at high frequency having a similar to P(O-2)(1/4) dependence.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: These features are attributed to dissociative oxygen adsorption and to charge transfer reactions, respectively.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure

Sentencas: Results suggest that Cathodic losses can be substantially lowered by operation Of solid Oxide fuel cells at greater than ambient pressure.
Titulo: Performance of lanthanum strontium manganite electrodes at high pressure
